  "conclusion": "The original P01d sample-6 negative sign reproduces, but it is not stable to shape-aware replacement. Train-run local curvature and the no-sample-6 ML imputer remove most of the favorable OF/template response, while the target-shuffle timing artifact shows that timing narrowing alone can be produced by bad sample-6 smoothing. Sample 6 is therefore better interpreted as a local shape/tuning artifact of the control replacement than as a standalone smoothing robustness claim.",
